-->5. Network Security Basics
-Firewalls: filter traffic and block unauthorized access.
-VPNs: create secure tunnels over the internet to protect confidentiality.
-HTTPS: secures web communication with TLS/SSL encryption.
-Port Scanning: identifies open ports on a system (using tools like Nmap) to detect vulnerabilities.
-Basic terminal commands (ping, traceroute, nmap) were introduced as practical tools.


==>Connections Between Concepts

>Encryption (symmetric and asymmetric) protects confidentiality.

>Digital signatures protect integrity and provide authentication.

>Network security tools like firewalls, VPNs, and HTTPS enforce the CIA Triad across systems.

>Port scanning highlights the importance of monitoring for potential entry points to maintain availability and reduce risk.